result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicholas N Camargo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Cause Child 13-18 to View Sex. Activity, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.055(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program. Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

miscConds.notes:
BOND SHALL BE APPLIED TO ATTORNEY FEES AND COSTS, ANY REMAINDER WILL BE RETURNED TO SURETY.
If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
No internet unless prior approval from agent.

Complete compas assessment,counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate and followup especially sex offender assessment.  Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections and follow rules of supervision.  Submit DNA sample. Pay court appointed attorney fees. Comply with Sex Offender Registry Program under 301.45, Wis. Stats.

timeConds.notes: Consecutive with good time and credit for 4 days time served. Huber granted, if in compliance with jail facility regulations.  Defendant shall report to the Work Release Unit (M-F/7:30 am to 3:30 pm), within 72 hours of sentence date with a copy of the minute sheet and the completed GPS application to establish report date for serving sentence.  Report date shall be within 60 days of sentence date.  Huber shall be revoked for failure to report and a warrant shall be authorized.
